<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12004o"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12004o">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12004o"> 4(o)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> his teeth / ciotoli from boots</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Alors que le souvenir des f&eacute;es et des nains plane sur les dolmens, celui de Gargantua est sp&eacute;cialement attach&eacute; aux menhirs. La plupart d&apos;entre eux sont en effet des graviers qui le g&ecirc;naient pour marcher, et dont il se d&eacute;barrassa en secouant sa chaussure. Ailleurs ces immenses pierres repr&eacute;sentent ses dents <br><font color="green">[If the memory of the fairies and dwarves hangs over the dolmens, the memory of Gargantua is specifically linked to the menhirs. Most of them are, in effect, pebbles [It. <i>ciottoli</i>]</font> that he shook from his shoe because they impeded him from walking. Elsewhere these immense rocks represent his teeth.] <small> l'Abb&eacute; A. Millon, <a name="AMPB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AMPB"><cite title="source">Pauvres Pierres! Les Megalithes Bretons devant la science</cite></a> (n.d) 14</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
